      <title>Rival monkey gangs wage street war over banana</title>
      <description><![CDATA[LOP BURI, THAILAND <br/> Rival monkey gangs fought a bitter street battle over a banana last week in Lop Buri Thailand, according to the Chiang Rai Times.<br/><br/>Citing a video posted to Twitter, the Thai outlet reports that monkeys can be seen fighting each other and chasing one who appears to have a banana. <br/><br/>According to the Bangkok Post, Lop Buri is home to two rival simian gangs, the temple monkeys and city monkeys. Each faction has their own turf.<br/><br/>The Chiang Rai Times reports that a slump in tourism to the popular temple area has led to a lack of food for the local monkey population who are usually fed by holidaygoers.<br/><br/>That, in turn, may have drove to the mass monkey brawl seen on social media last week.<br/><br/>According to Thai news site Khaosodo English, the monkeys are mostly fed high-sugar and fatty human foods.  All that junk food, the website reports, even led to one becoming obese. <br/><br/>WIKIMEDIA COMMONS<br/>https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Monkeys_at_Prang_Sam_Yot_(Monkey_Temple)_-_Lop_Buri_-_Thailand_-_05_(35028507555).jpg<br/>https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Monkey_Buffet_Lopburi_01.jpg  <br/>THUMB VIA FLICKR / JON RAWLINSON<br/>https://www.flickr.com/photos/london/25772226]]></description>
